The article is a transcript of a speech given by Vice President Kamala Harris at the Gaylord National Resort and Convention Center in National Harbor, Maryland. In her speech, Harris thanks the leaders in attendance and emphasizes the importance of their work in making progress for the Democratic party and the country. She highlights the achievements of the Democratic party over the past 18 months, including providing emergency relief during the pandemic, passing legislation to reduce healthcare and energy costs, expanding access to childcare, and confirming diverse judges to the federal courts. Harris also criticizes extremist leaders who are passing laws to restrict voting rights, attack the LGBTQ+ community, and limit women's reproductive rights. She urges Democrats to defend their majority in Congress and work towards passing important legislation such as the Freedom to Vote Act and the John Lewis Voting Rights Act. Harris concludes by urging Americans to stand with Democrats and fight for the rights and values they believe in.